:: dinerWork_event_vinceManagerPcSnoop_stubVincePersonal
<div class="divnobr">
<<set $location = "dinerRubysManagerOffice">>
<<jobEnsureState>>
<<updateCharacterLocations>>

<<set _todayKey = $timeSys.year * 10000 + $timeSys.month * 100 + $timeSys.day>>
<<if ndef $jobState.vincePcSnoopTimeDayKey>><<set $jobState.vincePcSnoopTimeDayKey = 0>><</if>>
<<if ndef $jobState.vincePcSnoopTimeLeftMin>><<set $jobState.vincePcSnoopTimeLeftMin = 30>><</if>>
<<if ndef $jobState.vincePcSnoopFolderPaid>><<set $jobState.vincePcSnoopFolderPaid = {}>><</if>>
<<if $jobState.vincePcSnoopTimeDayKey != _todayKey>>
    <<set $jobState.vincePcSnoopTimeDayKey = _todayKey>>
    <<set $jobState.vincePcSnoopTimeLeftMin = 30>>
    <<set $jobState.vincePcSnoopFolderPaid = {}>>
<</if>>

<<set _personalIntroCost = 2>>
<<set _personalDinerCost = 4>>
<<if !$jobState.vincePcSnoopFolderPaid.personal && $jobState.vincePcSnoopTimeLeftMin > 0>>
    <<set $jobState.vincePcSnoopFolderPaid.personal = true>>
    <<set $jobState.vincePcSnoopTimeLeftMin -= _personalIntroCost>>
    <<if $jobState.vincePcSnoopTimeLeftMin < 0>><<set $jobState.vincePcSnoopTimeLeftMin = 0>><</if>>
    <<advanceTime _personalIntroCost>>
<</if>>
<<set _pcTimePct = Math.floor(($jobState.vincePcSnoopTimeLeftMin / 30) * 100)>>
<<if _pcTimePct < 0>><<set _pcTimePct = 0>><</if>>
<<if _pcTimePct > 100>><<set _pcTimePct = 100>><</if>>

<<narrative "Personal / CC Statement">>
A PDF at the top of the folder. "CC_Aug_Sep.pdf." You open it.
<</narrative>>
<div class="quest-progress-label"><strong>Session time:</strong> <<= $jobState.vincePcSnoopTimeLeftMin>> / 30 min</div>
<div class="quest-progress-track"><div class="quest-progress-fill" style="width: <<= _pcTimePct>>%;"></div></div>

<<narrative>>
Personal card. Not the diner's. Two months, combined.

You start with August.
<br><br>
<span class="font-mono">
08/12 — GRAND MERIDIAN HOTEL . . . . $374.00<br>
08/20 — GOLDIE JEWELERS . . . . . . .$340.00<br>
08/23 — CRESTWOOD STEAKHOUSE . . . . $178.00<br>
08/25 — GRAND MERIDIAN HOTEL . . . . $187.00<br>
08/29 — HARBOR INN & SUITES . . . . .$156.00<br>
08/31 — FAMILY COURT — ORDER #4471 . $1,200.00
</span>
<</narrative>>

<<dialog "player">>
(Inner voice)
Grand Meridian. August 12th. $374.
<</dialog>>

<<narrative>>
Two nights.
<</narrative>>

<<dialog "player">>
(Inner voice)
That's Emma's hotel.
<</dialog>>

<<narrative>>
You look at the line above the Family Court payment. Goldie Jewelers, $340. Three days before.
<</narrative>>

<<dialog "player">>
(Inner voice)
Someone got jewelry that week.
<</dialog>>

<<narrative>>
September is shorter.
<br><br>
<span class="font-mono">
09/02 — HARBOR INN & SUITES . . . . .$156.00<br>
09/07 — CRESTWOOD STEAKHOUSE . . . . $203.00<br>
09/12 — GRAND MERIDIAN HOTEL . . . . $187.00
</span>
<</narrative>>

<<dialog "player">>
(Inner voice)
September 12th. Emma's bathroom clip. Same hotel, single night.
<</dialog>>

<<narrative>>
You scroll back to the top and just look at the full list for a second.
<</narrative>>

<<dialog "player">>
(Inner voice)
Child support, hotels, jewelry. All in the same month.
He's not hiding any of it. It's just… a normal month for him.
<</dialog>>

<div class="location-actions">
<<if $jobState.vincePcSnoopFolderPaid.personalDiner || $jobState.vincePcSnoopTimeLeftMin >= _personalDinerCost>>
<<btn "Continue" "dinerWork_event_vinceManagerPcSnoop_personal_diner" "secondary">><</btn>>
<<else>>
<span class="link-internal btn-style locked btn-secondary" data-tooltip="Need 4 min"><span class="icon icon-lock icon-12"></span> Continue</span>
<</if>>
<<btn "Back to folders" "dinerWork_event_vinceManagerPcSnoop" "secondary">><</btn>>
</div>
</div>